-- Ecopetrol Says Impact of Colombia Rebel Attacks Fell in July
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2012-08-09T21:46:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/ecopetrol-says-impact-of-colombia-rebel-attacks-fell-in-july.html
The impact of attacks by Colombia’s
Marxist rebels on  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL) , Colombia’s largest oil company,
fell in July compared with previous months, Chief Executive
Officer Javier Gutierrez said.  “We have had a very good month,” Gutierrez said in an
interview in Cartagena. “There were a few incidents, but it has
been a month that has improved significantly.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Bogota at 
